		<STRING> has developed the 3C's model..</STRING>
	</PARAGRAPH>
	<PARAGRAPH ID="2">
		<STRING>The 3C’s model points out that a strategist should focus on three key factors for success. In the construction of a business strategy, three main players must be taken into account:</STRING>
	</PARAGRAPH>
	<PARAGRAPH ID="3">
		<STRING>A.	The Corporation</STRING>
	</PARAGRAPH>
	<PARAGRAPH ID="4">
		<STRING>B.	The Customer</STRING>
	</PARAGRAPH>
	<PARAGRAPH ID="5">
		<STRING>C.	The Competitors</STRING>
	</PARAGRAPH>
	<PARAGRAPH ID="6">
		<STRING>Only by integrating these three C’s (Corporation, Customer, Competitors) in a strategic triangle, a sustained competitive advantage can exist. </STRING>
